 Nation at a Glance

 Karisma husband mailer charged

 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi police have chargesheeted 

 a Mumbai-based gangster for allegedly sending threatening 

 e-mails to actor Karisma Kapoors husband Sanjay Kapur 

 to extort Rs 50 crore. 

 The police had picked up Raj Kumar Vazirani and Sarvesh Kumar, owner of a cyber caf?, from Mumbai and made Kumar to depose on September 1. 

 He said the accused was in his cyber cafe on August 25 when the e-mail was sent. 

 In the mail, Vazirani, using the fake name of Sameer Kulkarni, had said he was writing on behalf of underworld don Ravi Pujari, a former Chhota Rajan associate, and threatened to kill the Delhi-based industrialist if he did not pay the money within a fortnight. 

 Health scheme told to pay up

 New Delhi (PTI): A consumer court has 

 ordered the Central Government Health Scheme (CGHS) to reimburse 

 the medical expenses of a retired government employee who 

 underwent an open-heart surgery at a private hospital here. 

 Diplal Sharma, 79, was paid only Rs 99,000 of the Rs 1.7 lakh he was billed by the Escorts Heart Institute and Research Centre in 2001. 

 The CGHS refused to pay him the remaining Rs 71,000, saying rules entitled him to get only Rs 99,000 for such an operation and that Escorts was not listed with it.

 Sharma moved the court on the ground that he went to Escorts only after getting permission from the CGHS. 

 The court asked the CGHS to pay the remaining amount, saying that it should revise its rates considering the increased cost of treatment. 

 Ayodhya case

 Ayodhya (PTI): Five persons accused 

 in the July 5 attack on the Ram Janmabhoomi complex have 

 been shifted to Naini central jail. 

 Dr Irfan, Asif Iqbal, Aziz, Shakeel and Naseem, who had been in the Faizabad district jail, were moved after authorities suggested a more secure prison for them.

 Pushkar fair

 Ajmer (PTI): A spiritual walk 

 around the ghats of the holy Pushkar lake and main temples 

 will be held on November 12 as part of the four-day Pushkar 

 fair. Foreign tourists and a large number of pilgrims are 

 expected to take part in the walk, sponsored by the Rajasthan 

 tourism board.

 Collision deaths

 Rajgarh (PTI): Seven persons were killed 

 when the jeep in which they were travelling collided with 

 a truck near Sarangpur, Madhya Pradesh, on Wednesday. One 

 person was critically injured.An unclaimed suitcase triggered 

 panic at the Chennai airport on Wednesday. Civil aviation 

 security personnel rushed to the spot but found only clothes 

 and a packet of sweets in it. 

